You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot microservice is experiencing gradual memory degradation leading to an `OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace` under heavy load. The following class is used to dynamically generate custom context-aware tenant proxies for database routing:

java
@Component
public class TenantRoutingProxyFactory {
    private static final ThreadLocal<ClassLoader> classLoaderTracker = new ThreadLocal<>();

    public Object createProxy(Object target, String tenantId) {
        ClassLoader dynamicClassLoader = new URLClassLoader(new URL[]{}, target.getClass().getClassLoader());
        classLoaderTracker.set(dynamicClassLoader);

        ProxyFactory factory = new ProxyFactory(target);
        factory.setProxyTargetClass(true); // Forces CGLIB
        return factory.getProxy(dynamicClassLoader);
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a high-concurrency Spring caching service experiences a silent memory leak under load. The developer attempted to implement an in-memory metadata cache using `WeakHashMap<SessionContext, Metadata>` to ensure that once a user's session is invalidated, the corresponding metadata is automatically garbage collected. However, heap dumps show millions of `Metadata` and `WeakReference` entries persisting even after sessions are terminated.

java
@Service
public class MetadataCacheService {
    private final Map<SessionContext, Metadata> cache = Collections.synchronizedMap(new WeakHashMap<>());

    public void cacheMetadata(SessionContext context, Metadata data) {
        context.setAssociatedMetadata(data); 
        cache.put(context, data);
    }
}
